Here are some smartphones available as of July 16, 2025, that meet your criteria of having an open-source operating system option (like /e/OS), NFC, an SD card slot, and long software updates.

**Smartphones with Good /e/OS Compatibility:**

*   **Fairphone:** Fairphone is specifically designed for repairability, sustainability, and compatibility with /e/OS [theprivacydad](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2) [murena](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3). The Murena Fairphone 4 comes with /e/OS pre-installed [murena](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3]. There is also a Fairphone 5 version with /e/OS [fairphone](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-4].
*   **/e/OS Compatibility:** /e/OS is based on LineageOS and works on a range of older smartphones [theprivacydad](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2). You can check the /e/OS documentation to see if your smartphone is supported [e](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5). If not, you can check for unofficial builds, but use them at your own risk [e](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-13). As of May 2024, /e/OS was compatible with 251 Android smartphones [murena](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1).

**Other Phones with NFC, SD Card Slot, and Long Updates:**

These phones may require manual installation of /e/OS or another open-source OS.

*   **Samsung Galaxy A35 5G:** This phone includes NFC, a microSD card slot, and a promise of four years of OS updates and five years of security updates [androidcentral](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0).
*   **Sony Xperia 1 VI:** This high-end device features NFC, a microSD card slot (up to 1.5TB), and a guarantee of three years of OS updates and four years of security updates [androidcentral](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0).
*   **CMF Phone 2 Pro:** This phone has NFC, a microSD card slot, and is guaranteed to receive three years of major OS updates and six years of security updates [androidcentral](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0).

**Open Source Alternatives (Not Android Based):**

*   **PinePhone:** This phone is designed for open-source enthusiasts, runs mainline Linux, and has hardware privacy switches [pine64](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-6). It has a microSD card slot and is supported by all major Linux phone projects [pine64](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-6) [pcmag](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-7).
*   **Librem 5:** This phone is built on PureOS, a fully free, ethical, and open-source operating system not based on Android or iOS [puri](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-8).

**Installing /e/OS:**

*   **/e/OS Easy Installer:** This desktop program simplifies the installation of /e/OS on compatible devices via USB [theprivacydad](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2).
*   **Manual Installation:** Advanced users can install /e/OS using Android platform tools [e](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-10) [e](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-11). This involves unlocking the bootloader and flashing a custom recovery manager [e](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-11).

**Important Considerations:**

*   Not all Android devices support custom ROMs, so check compatibility before installing [freedomtech](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2).
*   Installing custom ROMs may require some technical knowledge [fairphone](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-13). Find community support or an /e/OS install-party for help [e](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-13).
*   Other open-source Android alternatives include GrapheneOS, CalyxOS and LineageOS [intelivita](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-12) [freedomtech](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2) [gadgetsalvation](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3]. GrapheneOS is recommended for privacy and user-friendliness and can be easily installed on Google Pixel phones [reddit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-12).
